Malam Nuhu Ribadu, the Director,
Field Operations, Presidential Campaign Council (PCC), has commended
people of Adamawa for their peaceful conduct and maturity during
Saturday Presidential and National Assembly elections. Ribadu, also a former Chairman of
the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), gave the
commendation on Sunday while briefing newsmen in Yola. He said the peaceful conduct was a good development that showed the maturity of people of Adamawa. Ribadu said there was high hope for
APC victory in Adamawa, urging the politicians and their supporters to
accept the election outcomes with the spirit of sportsmanship. He lauded members of his team for their sacrifice in mobilising the electorate in Adamawa and other parts of the country. Ribadu said that they had supported a good cause. (NAN) Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA